[4] Thailand
Date: Wed 20 Aug 2008
Source: ScandAsia, Thailand News [edited]
<http://www.scandasia.com/viewNews.php?coun_code=th&news_id=4609>


The mosquito-carried virus [that causes] dengue fever, is raging with
massive force in Thailand and Southeast Asia. Thailand, especially
Koh Samet, Koh Mun, and Koh Kodi devastated by dengue fever, has been
written up by several Scandinavian newspapers in nearly identical
articles. This article from [Ekstra Bladet, Denmark] gives a general
understanding of the issues of dengue fever.

The latest official figures from the Thai authorities show that so
far 41 307 persons have been infected with dengue fever [viruses]
this year alone [2008]. When the authorities report on 41 307 cases,
it means the actual figure is at least 10 times higher, as the vast
majority will never be registered.

There are 48 reported deaths so far in 2008, compared to 29 deaths
throughout the whole year 2007, according to the Thai newspaper The
Nation.

[Byline: Bjarne Wildau]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur A-Lan Banks

