[5] Philippines (Pangasinan)
Date: Wed 20 Aug 2008
Source: ABS CBN News [edited]
<http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/storypage.aspx?StoryId=128803>


Health authorities on Wednesday [20 Aug 2008] declared a dengue
outbreak in Calasiao, Pangasinan after the number of suspected dengue
cases in the town went up to more than 100 since the start of the
year [2008].

Local health officials said they recorded 134 suspected dengue cases
in Calasiao from January to August this year [2008].

Results of tests conducted by the Department of Health showed that 2
out of 5 sampled patients have been afflicted with dengue-3 virus.

The DOH said it recorded a total of 720 suspected dengue cases in
Pangasinan this year [2008].

Mayor Roy Macanlalay and other local officials said parts of the
calamity fund would be used to step up the municipality's anti-
dengue campaign drive.

The local health office is also conducting cleaning operations of
mosquito breeding grounds in every village.

--
