[8] Indonesia (North Sumatra)
Date: Tue 19 Aug 2008
Source: Waspada Online [in Indonesian, machine trans., edited]
<http://www.waspada.co.id/Berita/Sumut/Korban-DBD-di-Tanjungbalai-terus-bertambah-warga-diminta-waspada.html>


Dengue fever has struck Tanjungbalai city [residents] from early
January [2008] until the present and continues to increase. Until
now, the count of the number of victims reached 165 and 44 people are
still under intensive care according to Dr T Mansyur Siagian.

This August [2008], there have been 70 cases and over the last 3 days
there have been 6 new patients as of 18 Aug 2008.

To prevent the [spread of dengue], said Dr Siagian, the residents must
continue to maintain the cleanliness of their environment and carry
out the "3 Ms", [closing, draining, and burying in the local language]
the mosquito breeding places in order to interrupt the dengue
epidemic. This method is one that was most effective in preventing the
spread of dengue fever, indicated Dr Siagian.

--
