[10] Trinidad & Tobago
Date: Thu 14 Aug 2008
Source: Trinidad & Tobago's Newsday [edited]
<http://www.newsday.co.tt/news/0,84347.html>


There are at least 3 confirmed cases of dengue being treated at the
San Fernando General Hospital (SFGH). Also, an 8-year-old girl died
over the weekend [9-10 Aug 2008] of the mosquito-borne disease, after
being hospitalised at the SFGH for 5 days. Earlier this year [2008],
another girl, of Tabaquite also succumbed to the disease.

According to hospital sources, several persons from Hindustan and
Princes Town are reported to be suffering from symptoms synonymous
with dengue.

One of the persons confirmed with the disease includes a fireman from
the Princes Town Fire Station, who was hospitalised for more than 15
days. He was discharged last week [week of 3 Aug 2008].

A hospital official noted that the number of dengue cases was nothing
out of the ordinary for this time of the year. He assured [the
public] that the patients were being treated accordingly.

[Byline: Felicia Rampersad]

--
