[11] Brazil (Rio de Janeiro)
Date: Wed 20 Aug 2008
Source: Maratimba [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod. TY, edited]
<http://www.portalmaratimba.com:80/noticias/news.php?codnot=236087>


The government has recorded 230 860 cases of the disease throughout
the state. Dengue fever has killed 162 people just in 2008, up to
this Wednesday [20 Aug 2008], in the state of Rio de Janeiro. The
number was confirmed by the state Secretariat of Health. Still under
investigation are 142 deaths.

According to the state Secretariat of Health, the largest number of
reported [dengue] cases is concentrated in the range of 15-49 years,
with 54 percent of the cases. Of the 162 deaths confirmed, 48 were
from DHF.

The city of Rio de Janeiro has the highest number of deaths, with 93.
The capital also has the majority of the [dengue] cases, totaling 120
358. The other municipalities with a large number of reported cases
are: Angra dos Reis (11 005[cases]), Campos (11 941), Nova Iguacu (17
393), Duque de Caxias (11 952), Sao Joao de Meriti (5653), Niteroi
(6829), Mage (3356), Belford Roxo (6755), and Sao Goncalo (2662).

--
